{"title_page": "Sarajevo School of Science and Technology", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name        = University Sarajevo School of Science and Technology\n|image       =\n|motto       = Inventing a Better Future\n|established = October 1, 2004\n|type        = [[Private university]]\n|staff       =\n|faculty     =\n|president   = [[Ejup Gani\u0107]], [[Ph.D.]]\n|students    =\n|undergrad   =\n|postgrad    =\n|city        = [[Sarajevo]]\n|country     = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n|campus      = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n|website     = [http://ssst.edu.ba/ www.ssst.edu.ba]\n|colors      = Red and White {{color box|#F00;}}&nbsp;{{color box|#ffffff}}\n}}\n'''Sarajevo School of Science and Technology''' ('''SSST''') is a [[private university]], located in metropolitan area of [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], within the municipality of [[Ilid\u017ea]], 10 miles west from [[Ba\u0161\u010dar\u0161ija]]. The university offers [[bachelor's degree]]s, [[master's degree]]s and [[doctorate degree]]s.\n\nThe university is in partnership with [[University of Buckingham]] of the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1M0y4HGaL-g</ref>\n\nThe Sarajevo School of Science and Technology is an English language-based university.\n\nOn 6 June 2018, the University Sarajevo School of Science and Technology (SSST) was ranked as one of the top 600 universities in the world and the best ranked university in the [[Balkan|Southeastern Europe]] ([[Slovenia]], [[Croatia]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Montenegro]], [[Albania]], [[Kosovo]], [[Serbia]], [[North Macedonia]], [[Romania]] and [[Bulgaria]]) on the [[QS World University Rankings]] for the upcoming 2019 year. SSST was on the 571st place while others, like [[University of Ljubljana]] was ranked as 651st and [[University of Zagreb]] and [[University of Belgrade]] shared the 801st position.<ref>https://ssst.edu.ba/news-single/358/university-sarajevo-school-of-science-and-technology---ssst--was-ranked-as-one-of-the-top-600-universities-in-the-world</ref>\n\n==Organization==\nThe seven departments into which the university is divided are as follows:\n\n* Department of [[Computer Science]]\n* Department of [[Information Systems]]\n* Department of [[Economics]]\n* Department of [[Political Science]] & [[International Relations]]\n* Department of [[Engineering Science]]\n* Department of [[Modern Languages]]\n* Sarajevo Film Academy\n* Sarajevo Medical School\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Sarajevo}}\n{{Bos_Uni}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sarajevo School Of Science And Technology}}\n[[Category:Education in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Universities in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Universities in Sarajevo]]\n[[Category:2004 establishments in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n\n\n{{BosniaHerzegovina-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name        = University Sarajevo School of Science and Technology\n|image       =\n|motto       = Inventing a Better Future\n|established = October 1, 2004\n|type        = [[Private university]]\n|staff       =\n|faculty     =\n|president   = [[Ejup Gani\u0107]], [[Ph.D.]]\n|students    =\n|undergrad   =\n|postgrad    =\n|city        = [[Sarajevo]]\n|country     = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n|campus      = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n|website     = [http://ssst.edu.ba/ www.ssst.edu.ba]\n|colors      = Red and White {{color box|#F00;}}&nbsp;{{color box|#ffffff}}\n}}\n'''Sarajevo School of Science and Technology''' ('''SSST''') is a [[private university]], located in metropolitan area of [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], within the municipality of [[Ilid\u017ea]], 10 miles west from [[Ba\u0161\u010dar\u0161ija]]. The university offers [[bachelor's degree]]s, [[master's degree]]s and [[doctorate degree]]s.\n\nThe university is in partnership with [[University of Buckingham]] of the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1M0y4HGaL-g</ref>\n\nThe Sarajevo School of Science and Technology is an English language-based university.\n\nOn 6 June 2018, the University Sarajevo School of Science and Technology (SSST) was ranked as one of the top 600 universities in the world and the best ranked university in the [[Balkan|Southeastern Europe]] ([[Slovenia]], [[Croatia]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Montenegro]], [[Albania]], [[Kosovo]], [[Serbia]], [[North Macedonia]], [[Romania]] and [[Bulgaria]]) on the [[QS World University Rankings]] for the upcoming 2019 year. SSST was on the 571st place while others, like [[University of Ljubljana]] was ranked as 651st and [[University of Zagreb]] and [[University of Belgrade]] shared the 801st position.<ref>https://ssst.edu.ba/news-single/358/university-sarajevo-school-of-science-and-technology---ssst--was-ranked-as-one-of-the-top-600-universities-in-the-world</ref>\n\n==Organization==\nThe seven departments into which the university is divided are as follows:\n\n* Department of [[Computer Science]]\n* Department of [[Information Systems]]\n* Department of [[Economics]]\n* Department of [[Political Science]] & [[International Relations]]\n* Department of [[Engineering Science]]\n* Department of [[Modern Languages]]\n* Sarajevo Film Academy\n* Sarajevo Medical School\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Sarajevo}}\n{{Bos_Uni}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sarajevo School Of Science And Technology}}\n[[Category:Education in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Universities in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Universities in Sarajevo]]\n[[Category:2004 establishments in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n\n\n{{BosniaHerzegovina-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarajevo_School_of_Science_and_Technology"}
{"title_page": "Sarajevo Graduate School of Business", "text_new": "{{infobox university\n|name        = Sarajevo Graduate School of Business\n|image       = \n|motto       = \n|established = February, 2004\n|type        = [[Private university|Private]]\n|staff       = \n|faculty     = \n|president   = Daniel Gies\n|students    = \n|undergrad   = \n|postgrad    = \n|city        = [[Sarajevo]]\n|country     = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n|campus      = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n|website     = [http://www.sgsb.ba/ www.sgsb.ba]\n|colors      = Red and White {{color box|#F00;}}&nbsp;{{color box|#ffffff}}\n}}\n'''Sarajevo Graduate School of Business''' ('''SGSB''') is a [[private university|private]] [[university]] located in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].  It is mainly focused on [[MBA]] degree.\n\nThe school is in partnership with [[Texas A&M University]] located in [[Commerce]], [[Texas]], [[United States]] and the [[International Burch University]] located in [[Sarajevo]].\n\n{{Bos_Uni}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Universities in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Universities in Sarajevo]]\n\n\n{{BosniaHerzegovina-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{infobox University\n|name        = Sarajevo Graduate School of Business\n|image       = \n|motto       = \n|established = February, 2004\n|type        = [[Private university|Private]]\n|staff       = \n|faculty     = \n|president   = Daniel Gies\n|students    = \n|undergrad   = \n|postgrad    = \n|city        = [[Sarajevo]]\n|country     = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n|campus      = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n|website     = [http://www.sgsb.ba/ www.sgsb.ba]\n|colors      = Red and White {{color box|#F00;}}&nbsp;{{color box|#ffffff}}\n}}\n'''Sarajevo Graduate School of Business''' ('''SGSB''') is a [[private university|private]] [[university]] located in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].  It is mainly focused on [[MBA]] degree.\n\nThe school is in partnership with [[Texas A&M University]] located in [[Commerce]], [[Texas]], [[United States]] and the [[International Burch University]] located in [[Sarajevo]].\n\n{{Bos_Uni}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Universities in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Universities in Sarajevo]]\n\n\n{{BosniaHerzegovina-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarajevo_Graduate_School_of_Business"}
{"title_page": "Santo Domingo Institute of Technology", "text_new": "{{Infobox university \n|image_name=Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo logo.jpg\n|image_size=150px\n|name=Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo\n|motto=Asume el Reto ([[Spanish language|Spanish]])\n|mottoeng=Accept the Challenge\n|established=October 9, 1972\n|type=[[Private university|Private]]\n|dean= Dr. Rolando Guzm\u00e1n\n|city = [[Santo Domingo]]\n|state=\n|country=[[Dominican Republic]]\n|students=\n|undergrad=\n|postgrad=\n|staff=\n|free_label      = \n|free            = \n|campus=[[Urban area|Urban]]\n|mascot=\n|colors= Red, White and Gray {{color box|#FF0000}} {{color box|#FFFFFF}}\n|athletics=\n|affiliations = [[Compostela Group of Universities]]\n|endowment=\n|website=http://www.intec.edu.do\n|logo = [[Image:Intec.png]]\n|}}\n'''Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo''' \u2014or '''Santo Domingo Institute of Technology''' (also known as '''INTEC'''), is a [[Private university|private]], [[coeducational]], university in [[Santo Domingo]], [[Dominican Republic]]. It was founded on October 9, 1972, by a group of connoted professional and is considered the best institute of technology in the country.<ref name=\"Ranking\">{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.webometrics.info/top50_latinamerica.asp?cont=centralamerica_caribe\n |title       = Latin American Universities' ranking on the Web Top Central America & Caribe\n |accessdate  = 2007-01-20\n |date        = July 2006\n |work        = Webometrics\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20070119110959/http://www.webometrics.info/top50_latinamerica.asp?cont=centralamerica_caribe\n |archivedate = 2007-01-19\n}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe University began with the intention to contribute to the social transformation of the country, the continuous improvement of the quality of life and the preservation of moral and material patrimony. It was incorporated legally as a non-profit organization by means of Presidential Decree no. 2389 on June 15, 1972. Its original academic activities included [[post-graduate]] programs, permanent education, and scientific research. In 1973, the university integrated other fields of study into its curriculum. Its current curricular structure is based on the System, offering academic programs in [[Engineering]], [[Business]] Administration, the [[Humanities]], [[Social Sciences]], and [[Medicine]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.intec.edu.do/ Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo]\n*[http://dr1.com/students/guide Dominican Republic Student & University Guide]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{coord missing|Dominican Republic}}\n{{Compostela Group of Universities}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Instituto Tecnologico de Santo Domingo}}\n[[Category:Universities in the Dominican Republic]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Santo Domingo]]\n[[Category:Education in Santo Domingo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox University \n|image_name=Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo logo.jpg\n|image_size=150px\n|name=Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo\n|motto=Asume el Reto ([[Spanish language|Spanish]])\n|mottoeng=Accept the Challenge\n|established=October 9, 1972\n|type=[[Private university|Private]]\n|dean= Dr. Rolando Guzm\u00e1n\n|city = [[Santo Domingo]]\n|state=\n|country=[[Dominican Republic]]\n|students=\n|undergrad=\n|postgrad=\n|staff=\n|free_label      = \n|free            = \n|campus=[[Urban area|Urban]]\n|mascot=\n|colors= Red, White and Gray {{color box|#FF0000}} {{color box|#FFFFFF}}\n|athletics=\n|affiliations = [[Compostela Group of Universities]]\n|endowment=\n|website=http://www.intec.edu.do\n|logo = [[Image:Intec.png]]\n|}}\n'''Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo''' \u2014or '''Santo Domingo Institute of Technology''' (also known as '''INTEC'''), is a [[Private university|private]], [[coeducational]], university in [[Santo Domingo]], [[Dominican Republic]]. It was founded on October 9, 1972, by a group of connoted professional and is considered the best institute of technology in the country.<ref name=\"Ranking\">{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.webometrics.info/top50_latinamerica.asp?cont=centralamerica_caribe\n |title       = Latin American Universities' ranking on the Web Top Central America & Caribe\n |accessdate  = 2007-01-20\n |date        = July 2006\n |work        = Webometrics\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20070119110959/http://www.webometrics.info/top50_latinamerica.asp?cont=centralamerica_caribe\n |archivedate = 2007-01-19\n}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe University began with the intention to contribute to the social transformation of the country, the continuous improvement of the quality of life and the preservation of moral and material patrimony. It was incorporated legally as a non-profit organization by means of Presidential Decree no. 2389 on June 15, 1972. Its original academic activities included [[post-graduate]] programs, permanent education, and scientific research. In 1973, the university integrated other fields of study into its curriculum. Its current curricular structure is based on the System, offering academic programs in [[Engineering]], [[Business]] Administration, the [[Humanities]], [[Social Sciences]], and [[Medicine]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.intec.edu.do/ Instituto Tecnol\u00f3gico de Santo Domingo]\n*[http://dr1.com/students/guide Dominican Republic Student & University Guide]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{coord missing|Dominican Republic}}\n{{Compostela Group of Universities}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Instituto Tecnologico de Santo Domingo}}\n[[Category:Universities in the Dominican Republic]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Santo Domingo]]\n[[Category:Education in Santo Domingo]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santo_Domingo_Institute_of_Technology"}
{"title_page": "Santiago Mari\u00f1o Polytechnic University Institute", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|{{unreferenced|date=June 2015}}{{lead too long|date=June 2015}}{{Advert|date=January 2016}}}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|name            = Santiago Mari\u00f1o Polytechnic University Institute \n|native_name     = Instituto Universitario Polit\u00e9cnico \"Santiago Mari\u00f1o\"\n|image           = IUP Santiago Mari\u00f1o.png\n|motto           = Training for excellence!\n|established     = September 17, 1991\n|founder         = Dr. Ra\u00fal Quero Silva\n|type            = [[Private university|Private]]\n|endowment       = \n|staff           =\n|rector          =\n|students        =\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|city            = [[Barcelona (Venezuela)|Barcelona]]\n|country         = [[Venezuela]]\n|campus          = Av. Intercomunal Andr\u00e9s Bello, Parroquia El Carmen, [[Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar, Anzo\u00e1tegui]].\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|affiliations    =\n|website         = http://psm.edu.ve\n}}\n[[File:PSM Matur\u00edn.jpg|thumb|Campus in [[Matur\u00edn]]]]\n[[File:PSM Merida.jpg|thumb|Campus in [[M\u00e9rida, M\u00e9rida|M\u00e9rida]]]]\n[[File:Sede Puerto Ordaz.jpg|thumb|Campus in [[Puerto Ordaz]]]]\n\nThe '''Santiago Mari\u00f1o Polytechnic University Institute''' (Spanish: Instituto Universitario Polit\u00e9cnico \"Santiago Mari\u00f1o\", '''IUPSM''') is a private university located in [[Barcelona (Venezuela)|Barcelona]], [[Venezuela]]. It belongs to a network of [[Higher education]] universities called \"Educational Complex \"Antonio Jos\u00e9 de Sucre\". The '''IUPSM''' is one of the universities with the most number of extensions in the whole country, fulfilling duties of imparting classes and investigation.\n\nIt offers to its students services like free dental health, student insurance, [[Scholarship]]s, sport activities, Venezuelan culture, recreational and orientation activities. It also counts with a large number of chemical, electrical and computer laboratories.\n\n== History ==\nThe institution was created on September 17, 1991 by Dr. Ra\u00fal Quero Silva in [[Barcelona (Venezuela)|Barcelona]] and it started its functions as a university by the presidential decree N\u00ba 1.893. The academic activities started for the first time on October, 1991 with [[Architecture]] and [[Engineering]] classes. On the year 1993, the institution expanded its coverage and educational offer by creating extensions in different cities.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of universities in Venezuela]]\n* [[Santiago Mari\u00f1o]]\n*{{commons category-inline|Instituto Universitario Polit\u00e9cnico Santiago Mari\u00f1o}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord missing|Venezuela}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santiago Marino Polytechnic University Institute}}\n[[Category:Universities in Venezuela]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Anzo\u00e1tegui]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Monagas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|{{unreferenced|date=June 2015}}{{lead too long|date=June 2015}}{{Advert|date=January 2016}}}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|name            = Santiago Mari\u00f1o Polytechnic University Institute \n|native_name     = Instituto Universitario Polit\u00e9cnico \"Santiago Mari\u00f1o\"\n|image           = IUP Santiago Mari\u00f1o.png\n|motto           = Training for excellence!\n|established     = September 17, 1991\n|founder         = Dr. Ra\u00fal Quero Silva\n|type            = [[Private university|Private]]\n|endowment       = \n|staff           =\n|rector          =\n|students        =\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|city            = [[Barcelona (Venezuela)|Barcelona]]\n|country         = [[Venezuela]]\n|campus          = Av. Intercomunal Andr\u00e9s Bello, Parroquia El Carmen, [[Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar, Anzo\u00e1tegui]].\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|affiliations    =\n|website         = http://psm.edu.ve\n}}\n[[File:PSM Matur\u00edn.jpg|thumb|Campus in [[Matur\u00edn]]]]\n[[File:PSM Merida.jpg|thumb|Campus in [[M\u00e9rida, M\u00e9rida|M\u00e9rida]]]]\n[[File:Sede Puerto Ordaz.jpg|thumb|Campus in [[Puerto Ordaz]]]]\n\nThe '''Santiago Mari\u00f1o Polytechnic University Institute''' (Spanish: Instituto Universitario Polit\u00e9cnico \"Santiago Mari\u00f1o\", '''IUPSM''') is a private university located in [[Barcelona (Venezuela)|Barcelona]], [[Venezuela]]. It belongs to a network of [[Higher education]] universities called \"Educational Complex \"Antonio Jos\u00e9 de Sucre\". The '''IUPSM''' is one of the universities with the most number of extensions in the whole country, fulfilling duties of imparting classes and investigation.\n\nIt offers to its students services like free dental health, student insurance, [[Scholarship]]s, sport activities, Venezuelan culture, recreational and orientation activities. It also counts with a large number of chemical, electrical and computer laboratories.\n\n== History ==\nThe institution was created on September 17, 1991 by Dr. Ra\u00fal Quero Silva in [[Barcelona (Venezuela)|Barcelona]] and it started its functions as a university by the presidential decree N\u00ba 1.893. The academic activities started for the first time on October, 1991 with [[Architecture]] and [[Engineering]] classes. On the year 1993, the institution expanded its coverage and educational offer by creating extensions in different cities.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of universities in Venezuela]]\n* [[Santiago Mari\u00f1o]]\n*{{commons category inline|Instituto Universitario Polit\u00e9cnico Santiago Mari\u00f1o}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord missing|Venezuela}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santiago Marino Polytechnic University Institute}}\n[[Category:Universities in Venezuela]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Anzo\u00e1tegui]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Monagas]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "